00:40:12.954 --> 00:40:14.870
AUDIENCE: It was mentioned
in the introduction

00:40:14.870 --> 00:40:17.030
that you had been involved
with the slow food movement.

00:40:17.030 --> 00:40:19.405
And I was hoping you could
talk a bit about what that is,

00:40:19.405 --> 00:40:24.050
and what impact, if any, it's
had on your cookbook writing?

00:40:24.050 --> 00:40:26.360
DEBORAH MADISON: I don't
know what kind of impact

00:40:26.360 --> 00:40:28.960
Slow Food has had on my writing.

00:40:28.960 --> 00:40:31.080
Slow Food started,
actually when I

00:40:31.080 --> 00:40:33.680
was living in Rome
in the mid '80s,

00:40:33.680 --> 00:40:40.650
as a response to McDonald's
opening on the Spanish steps.

00:40:40.650 --> 00:40:42.330
And that was very
painful to a lot

00:40:42.330 --> 00:40:43.950
of Italians, the Spanish steps?

00:40:43.950 --> 00:40:45.060
McDonald's?

00:40:45.060 --> 00:40:47.940
And so a group got
together, and they

00:40:47.940 --> 00:40:51.232
made pasta bolognese,
or some kind of pasta.

00:40:51.232 --> 00:40:53.190
And they stood in front
of McDonald's, and they

00:40:53.190 --> 00:40:54.190
said, don't eat that.

00:40:54.190 --> 00:40:57.720
Have some of this.

00:40:57.720 --> 00:41:01.380
It really started because so
many of the little trattorias

00:41:01.380 --> 00:41:04.730
or cafes were closing.

00:41:04.730 --> 00:41:05.720
They no longer existed.

00:41:08.490 --> 00:41:10.440
People were going for fast food.

00:41:10.440 --> 00:41:12.840
And they didn't want to lose
that part of their culture.

00:41:12.840 --> 00:41:15.190
The same thing has
happened here by the way.

00:41:15.190 --> 00:41:19.450
It's very hard to find a good
family a Cafe, very hard.

00:41:19.450 --> 00:41:21.340
It's mostly just awful.

00:41:21.340 --> 00:41:25.850
And so the movement
started with that,

00:41:25.850 --> 00:41:28.640
and then it grew to,
well what about our foods

00:41:28.640 --> 00:41:31.260
and other customs,
and not just Italy,

00:41:31.260 --> 00:41:35.650
but Europe, the U.S., China,
all kinds of countries

00:41:35.650 --> 00:41:39.440
have lost many of their
foods, and how can they

00:41:39.440 --> 00:41:40.895
be brought back and appreciated?

00:41:40.895 --> 00:41:42.920
It was about slowing down.

00:41:42.920 --> 00:41:46.640
Anyway, it's hard to find an
