00:41:51.490 --> 00:41:53.740
And then something clicks.

00:41:53.740 --> 00:41:56.520
They've heard of fast
food, so slow food

00:41:56.520 --> 00:42:00.410
is saying something to them.

00:42:00.410 --> 00:42:04.690
I have been involved with Slow
Food for a really long time.

00:42:04.690 --> 00:42:07.260
I used to wear a lot of
hats in that organization,

00:42:07.260 --> 00:42:09.350
but the most
important one to me,

00:42:09.350 --> 00:42:11.560
was the Ark and
Presidia committee,

00:42:11.560 --> 00:42:14.900
which was very involved with
identifying those foods that

00:42:14.900 --> 00:42:18.520
had historical and
gustatory significance.

00:42:18.520 --> 00:42:20.575
And in America, we
have lots of them.

00:42:20.575 --> 00:42:23.700
We have lots of apples, and
plums, and fruits, and grains,

00:42:23.700 --> 00:42:26.470
and all animal breeds,
all kinds of foods

00:42:26.470 --> 00:42:30.110
that have disappeared for
just something bigger, faster,

00:42:30.110 --> 00:42:31.640
cheaper, whatever.

00:42:31.640 --> 00:42:35.020
So it's been very involved
in bringing these foods back.

00:42:35.020 --> 00:42:39.340
They're a part of my pantry
to the degree that I can.

00:42:39.340 --> 00:42:43.302
So I would say has it has
introduced me to food.

00:42:43.302 --> 00:42:45.760
